scene.message:
Maki: It's a pretty painting.{nl}
But I'm not really{nl}
all that fond of it...{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: Was this really{nl}
for the best, I wonder?{wait_fr:32}{nl}
Hey, what do you think,{nl}
{ctl07:1}...?{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: I don't know much{nl}
about paintings, but...{waitkey}{clearbox}Unlike Sonomura's painting,{nl}
there's nothing in this one{nl}
that stirs the heart.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: So it was Kozai...{nl}
But how did she become{nl}
the ruler of this market?{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Fawning over Kozai{nl}
one moment, and once she's{nl}
gone, trashing her freely...{waitkey}How quickly they turn.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: This painting looks{nl}
good at a glance, right?{nl}
But that's not enough.{waitkey}{clearbox}It's not technique. Cheesy{nl}
as it sounds, a painting's{nl}
all about heart!{waitkey}{clearbox}This one's all surface.{nl}
There's not a shred of the{nl}
painter's heart in it!{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Kozai, why are you{nl}
lending Aki a hand?{nl}
Ditching Naito and all...{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Maybe Sonomura's not{nl}
as down as we're worried{nl}
she is. I hope that's so.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: A harem, meaning a place{nl}
where wonderful men are{nl}
gathered, I suppose?{waitkey}{clearbox}But Miss Kozai already{nl}
has a boyfriend, doesn't she.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: You never really know{nl}
what people say behind{nl}
your back, don't you think?{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: Paintings are so{nl}
boring~{wait_fr:32}{nl}
...Yeah, this is a really{nl}
boring painting.{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: That Kozai just now{nl}
was kinda cute, maybe...{waitkey}Just kidding! Kidding!{nl}
And Naito, of all people!{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Is that boy part of{nl}
the Queen's harem too~?{nl}
No way, so unfair!{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Kozai must've been{nl}
hurting too, y'know.{nl}
Try to understand that.{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Ayase wants that{nl}
mirror too, but I'd hate to{nl}
get any more freckles.{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: Whoever made such a{nl}
worthless room must be{nl}
awfully childish.{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: Believing in something{nl}
like friendship is the{nl}
strange part, isn't it?{nl}
It's all just for show.{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: In any case, it's{nl}
resolved, isn't it?{nl}
No need to linger...{waitkey}{ret}

Young Man: This is a painting{nl}
by Lady Queen. Pretty{nl}
amazing, right?{waitkey}{clearbox}Lady Queen's got a gift{nl}
for painting, and she's{nl}
beautiful too!{waitkey}{clearbox}She's got loads of moles,{nl}
and boy is she gorgeous!{waitkey}{clearbox}She showed me a painting by{nl}
an acquaintance of hers once,{nl}
but that one was lousy!{waitkey}{ret}

Young Man: How does she dare{nl}
show people such a{nl}
worthless painting!{waitkey}'Queen,' my foot!{waitkey}{ret}

There's a painting said to{nl}
be by the Queen.{wait_fr:21}{nl}
...The style looks like{nl}
something I've seen before.{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: ...{wait_fr:32}This painting...!{wait_fr:48}{nl}
This is one Chisato{nl}
painted...!{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Chisato as in {wait_fr:21}Chisato{nl}
Kozai? I heard she went{nl}
missing!{waitkey}{clearbox}Kozai's painting is here,{nl}
and you're saying it's{nl}
the Queen's painting...?{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: Why?{wait_fr:48}{nl}
So Chisato's been{nl}
taken by the Harem{nl}
Queen...?{wait_fr:32}{waitkey}{ret}
